==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whitish
<hw>Whit"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From <er>White</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Somewhat white; approaching white; white in a
moderate degree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Covered with an opaque white
powder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whitishness</ent>⟦br⟧
